.TH RTPARITYD 1 "2025" "rtparityd 0.1" "rtparityd daemon"
.SH NAME
rtparityd \- RAID-like parity daemon for data integrity and durability
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rtparityd
[\fB\-\-config\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-socket\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-admin\-socket\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-pid\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-pool\-name\fR \fINAME\fR]
[\fB\-\-journal\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-metadata\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-require\-root\fR]
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rtparityd
is a production-grade storage daemon that provides data protection through
parity-based redundancy. It manages extents across multiple disks,
automatically rebuilds missing data from parity, and ensures durability
through journaled writes and metadata snapshots.
.PP
The daemon exposes a Unix socket control interface for client operations
and an admin socket for administrative tasks. All operations are logged
and audited.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-config " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to TOML configuration file. Optional.
.TP
.BR \-\-socket " " \fIPATH\fR
Unix socket path for client control interface (default: /var/run/rtparityd/rtparityd.sock)
.TP
.BR \-\-admin\-socket " " \fIPATH\fR
Unix socket path for admin interface (default: none)
.TP
.BR \-\-pid\-file " " \fIPATH\fR
PID file path (default: /var/run/rtparityd/rtparityd.pid)
.TP
.BR \-\-pool\-name " " \fINAME\fR
Pool name (default: demo)
.TP
.BR \-\-journal\-path " " \fIPATH\fR
Journal file path (default: /var/lib/rtparityd/journal.bin)
.TP
.BR \-\-metadata\-path " " \fIPATH\fR
Metadata file path (default: /var/lib/rtparityd/metadata.bin)
.TP
.BR \-\-require\-root
Require root user for socket connections (default: true)
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show version and exit
.SH OPERATIONS
Client operations are sent as JSON over the control socket:
.PP
.BR write
\- Write data to the pool
.RS
.PP
\fBParams:\fR path, size, payload (optional), synthetic (bool)
.RE
.PP
.BR read
\- Read data from the pool
.RS
.PP
\fBParams:\fR path
.RE
.PP
.BR bulk\-write
\- Write multiple files in batch
.RS
.PP
\fBParams:\fR paths[], size, payload, synthetic
.RE
.PP
.BR bulk\-read
\- Read multiple files in batch
.RS
.PP
\fBParams:\fR paths[]
.RE
.PP
.BR health
\- Overall health status with component details
.PP
.BR liveness
\- Simple alive/dead check
.PP
.BR readiness
\- Detailed readiness probe
.PP
.BR metrics
\- Internal metrics snapshot (JSON)
.PP
.BR prometheus
\- Metrics in Prometheus format
.PP
.BR disk\-stats
\- Per-disk statistics
.PP
.BR pool\-stats
\- Pool capacity and extent information
.PP
.BR memory\-pool\-stats
\- Go runtime memory statistics
.PP
.BR locks
\- Lock file information
.PP
.BR config\-get
\- Current runtime configuration
.PP
.BR state\-dump
\- Full daemon state for debugging
.PP
.BR scrub
\- Verify and repair data integrity
.RS
.PP
\fBParams:\fR repair (bool, default false)
.RE
.PP
.BR rebuild
\- Rebuild single disk from parity
.RS
.PP
\fBParams:\fR disk_id
.RE
.PP
.BR rebuild\-all
\- Rebuild all disks
.PP
.BR backup
\- Create backup of metadata and journal
.RS
.PP
\fBParams:\fR output_path
.RE
.PP
.BR restore
\- Restore from backup
.RS
.PP
\fBParams:\fR input_path
.RE
.PP
.BR reload\-config
\- Hot reload configuration
.RS
.PP
\fBParams:\fR config_path
.RE
.PP
.BR check\-consistency
\- Run integrity invariants check
.PP
.BR repair\-metadata
\- Attempt metadata repair
.PP
.BR compact\-journal
\- Compact journal to reduce size
.PP
.BR recover\-status
\- Recovery operation status
.PP
.BR host\-info
\- Host system information
.PP
.BR system\-stats
\- System resource statistics
.PP
.BR validate\-config
\- Validate configuration file
.RS
.PP
\fBParams:\fR config_path
.RE
.PP
.BR operations
\- List all available operations
.PP
.BR batch
\- Execute multiple operations in one request
.RS
.PP
\fBParams:\fR commands[]
.RE
.PP
.BR version
\- Daemon version information
.PP
.BR ping
\- Simple ping/pong
.SH ADMIN OPERATIONS
Admin operations require root access via the admin socket:
.PP
.BR shutdown
\- Gracefully shutdown daemon
.PP
.BR drain
\- Enter drain mode (reject new writes)
.PP
.BR status
\- Admin status information
.PP
.BR force\-gc
\- Force Go garbage collection
.SH CONFIGURATION
