Scrub window end
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/rtparityd/rtparityd.conf
Default configuration file
.TP
.I /var/run/rtparityd/rtparityd.sock
Control socket
.TP
.I /var/run/rtparityd/rtparityd-admin.sock
Admin socket
.TP
.I /var/run/rtparityd/rtparityd.pid
PID file
.TP
.I /var/lib/rtparityd/journal.bin
Journal file
.TP
.I /var/lib/rtparityd/metadata.bin
Metadata snapshot
.TP
.I /var/log/rtparityd/audit.log
Audit log
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Start daemon with default settings:
.PP
.nf
.B rtparityd
.fi
.PP
Start with custom configuration:
.PP
.nf
.B rtparityd --config /etc/rtparityd/rtparityd.conf
.fi
.PP
Check health:
.PP
.nf
.B echo '{"id":"1","op":"health"}' | socat - UNIX-CONNECT:/var/run/rtparityd/rtparityd.sock
.fi
.PP
Write data:
.PP
.nf
.B echo '{"id":"1","op":"write","params":{"path":"/file","size":1024}}' | \\
    socat - UNIX-CONNECT:/var/run/rtparityd/rtparityd.sock
.fi
.PP
Graceful shutdown:
.PP
.nf
.B echo '{"id":"1","op":"shutdown"}' | \\
    socat - UNIX-CONNECT:/var/run/rtparityd/rtparityd-admin.sock
.fi
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
Use the
.B health
operation to check component status. The response includes:
.IP \(bu 2
journal: records count, replay requirement
.IP \(bu 2
metadata: files, extents, disks counts
.IP \(bu 2
disk: failed/degraded disk counts
.IP \(bu 2
memory: runtime memory stats
.PP
Enable debug logging by setting level to "debug" in config.
.SH ERROR CODES
.TP
1001
Invalid parameters
.TP
1002
Not found
.TP
1003
Internal error
.TP
1004
Rate limited (try again later)
.TP
1005
Timeout
.TP
1006
Not implemented
.TP
1007
Permission denied
.TP
1008
Invalid state
